President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 20, 2016, as National Defense Transportation Day and May 15 through May 21, 2016, as National Transportation Week. In the proclamation, Obama emphasizes the importance of infrastructure in our country's history and the need to invest in transportation systems for the future. He highlights the role of infrastructure projects in driving innovation and economic growth, as well as uplifting the nation during times of crisis. The proclamation also emphasizes the importance of rebuilding and modernizing roads, bridges, ports, and water systems, as well as investing in a clean transportation system to combat climate change. Obama calls on all Americans to recognize the contributions of those who build, operate, and maintain our transportation infrastructure.